#------------------------------------

 What is K2?

#------------------------------------

 An Apple IIe/c presentation program

   *{GREY2}(Press space to show points)

 + Displays *{MEDIUM_BLUE}multi**{GREEN}colou**{MAGENTA}red* text if an
   A2DVI or Video7 compatible board
   provides the output

 + Uses mousetext characters for
   boxes, bullets and _underlining_

#BUILD: all
#------------------------------------

 User control

#------------------------------------

 + Right arrow "->" for next slide

 + Left arrow "<-" for previous
   slide

 + Spacebar will show successive
   points - if build by points
   enabled

 + If the slide is complete, spacebar
   moves to the next slide

 + Onscreen arrows indicate next and
   previous slides

 + "Q" to quit
#TITLE: left, none
#CONTENT: yellow/black
#------------------------------------

 Slide styling

#------------------------------------

 + Styling is determined by ...

   + commands, starting with *{WHITE}#

 + Commands include

   + Slide foreground and background
     colours e.g. *{white}#SLIDE: white/black

   + Title justification, border and
     colours *{white}#TITLE: centre, line,
                     *{white}light\_blue/black

   + Content border and colours
     *{white}#CONTENT: none, grey1/grey2

#BULLET: cross, magenta
#------------------------------------

 Commands

#------------------------------------

 + foreground/background colours
   any *{WHITE}combination* of *{WHITE}colours* (later)

   + applies to slide, title, content

 + title justification

   + *{WHITE}left, centre, right

 + title and contents outline

   + *{WHITE}line, none

 + bullet shapes and colours

   + e.g. *{WHITE}cross, magenta
#BULLET: diamond, orange
#BUILD: point
#------------------------------------

 Content Styling and Themes

#------------------------------------

 + The content can be styled with

   + *{purple}coloured* *{pink}text

   + _underlining_

 + Bullets can be a variety of
   mousetext characters

   And in different colours

 + Content can be presented point by
   point or all at once using the
   *{white}#BUILD:* command

 + It is easy to have themes
#BULLET: diamond, orange
#BUILD: all
#------------------------------------

 Slide layout

#------------------------------------

 + Layout is determined by ...

   + spacing you include in the text

   + this way the text source
     document is largely WYSIWYG

  the next slide shows the _source_ of
             this one

#SLIDE: white/black
#CONTENT: none, white/black
